## Anti-glossary (terms we explicitly DON'T use)

| Avoid | Use instead | Why |
|---|---|---|
| "user" (when a specific role is meant) | "buyer" / "seller" / "admin" | Specificity reduces ambiguity |
| "page" (in code) | "module" / "route" | Matches admin module anatomy |

## Naming conventions

- Database table: snake_case (`non_conformity`)
- TypeScript type: PascalCase (`NonConformity`)
- API path: kebab-case (`/admin/non-conformities/bulk-print`)
- React component: PascalCase (`NonConformitiesPage`)
- File: kebab-case (`non-conformities.tsx`)
- Permission resource: PascalCase (`NonConformities`)
- Permission action: PascalCase (`BulkPrint`)
